I picked the base number 1.737 (rounded to 1.74) because I like the numbers 17  37 and try to use them in all my SCPs. The other 3 numbers are rounded-off multiples of 1.737 (x1, x4, x9, x16). A lot of mystery cults were about that sacred mathematics, bro.

I thought about using the product rather than the sum, and the first few drafts actually DID use it, but I figured that it was too large for what I was going for, which was that the mystery cult was basically using it to sanctify their temple because they were Super Special. It still affected areas above the underground temple (52m radius is still pretty damn big!), but any larger and they wouldn't have been able to hide it as a cult secret/mystery.








